#MEM id=visual-style-integrity source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/skills/custom/visual-style-integrity/SKILL.md
M|visual-style-integrity|name: visual-style-integrity
M|visual-style-integrity|description: Structured "every element justifies itself" check using Dieter Rams principles. Strip test, 3-year test, and vtr drift check. Run during style spec dev to catch decoration masquerading as
M|visual-style-integrity|version: 1.0.0
M|visual-style-integrity|The most common failure in visual direction is adding rather than removing. A mood board with 12 references isn't richer — it's unfocused. A style spec with 6 lighting modifiers isn't precise — it's i
M|visual-style-integrity|For every element in the style spec — colour specification, lighting modifier, mood adjective, compositional rule, model direction, prop — ask:
M|visual-style-integrity|> "If I remove this element, does the image communicate something meaningfully different?"
M|visual-style-integrity|| Answer | Action |
M|visual-style-integrity||--------|--------|
M|visual-style-integrity|| Yes — removing it loses something specific | Keep it. It earns its place. |
M|visual-style-integrity|| No — the image works without it | Remove it. It's decoration. |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Unsure | Default to remove. Doubt = out. |
M|visual-style-integrity|**Elements to test explicitly:**
M|visual-style-integrity|- Each mood adjective (if 2 adjectives say the same thing, remove one)
M|visual-style-integrity|- Each lighting modifier (do you need both `soft` and `diffused`?)
M|visual-style-integrity|- Each colour in the palette (is each colour doing something different?)
M|visual-style-integrity|- Each composition rule (do they conflict or reinforce each other?)
M|visual-style-integrity|- Each item in the subject description (does every detail matter for this cg?)
M|visual-style-integrity|**Target:** A style spec that passes the strip test has no redundant elements. Every word is doing work.
M|visual-style-integrity|> "Would this visual direction still feel right in 2029?"
M|visual-style-integrity|**Failure signals (date this direction):**
M|visual-style-integrity|- The aesthetic is rooted in a specific soc media trend or moment (specific filter style, pose trend, viral format)
M|visual-style-integrity|- The direction references a cultural moment that will be resolved or forgotten
M|visual-style-integrity|- The AI generation style is visibly "2026 AI" — identifiable as a specific era of generative imagery
M|visual-style-integrity|- The colour palette is trending now but is not anchored to the brand palette
M|visual-style-integrity|- The composition style is borrowed from a specific creator or movement that peaked recently
M|visual-style-integrity|**Pass signals (direction is durable):**
M|visual-style-integrity|- The aesthetic is rooted in the brand's values, not in what's currently performing
M|visual-style-integrity|- The references are timeless visual traditions (editorial photography, Bauhaus reduction, Scandinavian minimalism)
M|visual-style-integrity|- The mood could describe photographs made in 2015 and photographs made in 2030 equally well
M|visual-style-integrity|- The colour palette is the brand palette — not the trend palette
M|visual-style-integrity|**If it fails the 3-year test:** Strip the trend element and re-anchor to a brand principle. The question to ask: "What does Novizio/Hourbour stand for that will still be true in 2029?" That's the dir
M|visual-style-integrity|Ventures drift when visual directions start to sound like other brands. Run this check before finalising.
M|visual-style-integrity|**Novizio drift: editorial minimalism → catalogue energy**
M|visual-style-integrity|| Drift signal | Correction |
M|visual-style-integrity||-------------|-----------|
M|visual-style-integrity|| Multiple products in one frame | One hero product or no product — editorial perspective |
M|visual-style-integrity|| White or plain background instead of contextual setting | Add environment: textured wall, natural setting, editorial space |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Model not engaging naturally with the product | Direction: authentic interaction, not demonstration |
M|visual-style-integrity|| High-key, flat, even lighting | Restore: soft, directional, natural — a single light source |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Text overlay or promotional element in image composition | Remove entirely — copy lives outside the image |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Perfect symmetry and commercial polish | Introduce considered imperfection — editorial is not symmetrical |
M|visual-style-integrity|**Hourbour drift: clean/modern → generic fintech cliché**
M|visual-style-integrity|| Drift signal | Correction |
M|visual-style-integrity||-------------|-----------|
M|visual-style-integrity|| Any money imagery (coins, notes, piggy banks) | Replace with person + device in a real working environment |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Dark dramatic backgrounds | Restore: white space, natural light, clean surfaces |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Corporate setting (boardroom, suits, handshakes) | Replace with solo professional, home office, focused ctx |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Upward graphs or checkmarks as visual elements | Remove — let the copy carry the outcome claim, not the image |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Generic phone mockup (floating device, no ctx) | Ground it: device in hand, on a real desk, with a real person |
M|visual-style-integrity|| Clinical or sterile feel | Add warmth: a plant, a coffee, a real workspace detail |
M|visual-style-integrity|Before closing: answer this in one sentence —
M|visual-style-integrity|> "The single most important thing this visual communicates is: ___"
M|visual-style-integrity|- If you can answer in one clear sentence → direction is focused. Proceed.
M|visual-style-integrity|- If the answer is "it looks good" or "it's on brand" → direction isn't done. Good and on-brand are prerequisites, not purposes.
M|visual-style-integrity|- If you can't answer → the direction needs more reduction before it goes to Pixel.
M|visual-style-integrity|```
M|visual-style-integrity|Strip test: [X elements tested] — [Y removed] — [reason for each removal]
M|visual-style-integrity|3-year test: [pass / fail] — [what was stripped or why it holds]
M|visual-style-integrity|Drift check: [clean / drift found: X corrected to Y]
M|visual-style-integrity|Purpose anchor: "The single most important thing this visual communicates is: ___"
M|visual-style-integrity|Style spec status: FINALISED / REVISED — see updated spec below
M|visual-style-integrity|```